# {{name}}

A mountly vertical widget scaffolded with `npx mountly init`.

## Develop

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm dev
```

## Build

```bash
pnpm build
```

Outputs:

- `dist/index.js` — self-contained (React/Vue/Svelte bundled)
- `dist/peer.js` — peer build (host supplies framework via import map)

## Publish to your CDN

Upload `dist/peer.js` (and source map) to your CDN, then register the URL in your host manifest:

```json
{
  "id": "{{name}}",
  "url": "https://cdn.example.com/{{name}}@1.0.0/dist/peer.js"
}
```

See [mountly micro-frontends docs](https://github.com/jagreehal/mountly/blob/main/docs/micro-frontends.md).
